turn.0: Hi, I'm your automated assistant. I can answer your questions about Shackspace.
turn.1: What events took place at Shackspace?
turn.2: The shackspace society is also present at events of the Chaos Computer Club, such as the Chaos Communication Congress, Chaos Communication Camp, Gulaschprogrammiernacht (GPN) and many others. shackspace is also used by other initiatives and groups in and around Stuttgart to host events (tech talks, workshops, project demos, and parties), such as Thunder Talks, Java and Python workshops, public viewing of Google I/O and worldwide HTML5 Campout in collaboration with Google Developer Group Stuttgart, regular meetups of the Linux User Group Stuttgart (LUGS), KDE Code Sprint, NASA International Space Apps Challenge.
turn.3: Did they host any other events?
turn.4: Any group that identifies themselves with the purpose of the shackspace are also welcome to use the location for meetups and events.
turn.5: What other activities took place there?
turn.6: Besides the main purpose of the shackspace association, the members are also engaged in many other activities, for example an urban art workshop, rhetoric workshop, and chemistry experiments.
turn.7: Did they have any other events?
turn.8: Once a year,an open-house event gives an overview of all activities offered.
turn.9: What other events did they have?
turn.10: There is also the regular weekly night social event, Plenum, that provides a good chance to meet people, talk about projects, and take a look around.
turn.12: shackspace is currently located at Ulmer Straße 255 in Wangen (Stuttgart).
